#- 
§0Gil-galad was§0
§0an Elven-king.§0
§0
§0Of him the harpers§0
§0sadly sing:§0
§0
§0The last whose realm§0
§0was fair and free§0
§0
§0Between the mountains and the sea.
#- 
§0His sword was long, his lance was keen.§0
§0
§0His shining helm§0
§0afar was seen.§0
§0
§0The countless stars of heaven's field§0
§0
§0Were mirrored in§0
§0his silver shield.
#- 
§0But long ago§0
§0he rode away,§0
§0
§0And where he dwelleth none can say.§0
§0
§0For into darkness§0
§0fell his star;§0
§0
§0In Mordor, where§0
§0the shadows are.
#- 